Not every rep was pretty but every rep had its purpose! Working on increasing Speed Strength today on the bench press. (1 - 1.3 meters per second bar speeds). Using the reverse banded technique, you’re simply giving yourself more assistance at the bottom of the rep, and are left to your own strength near the top of the rep as the band has less tension against the barbell. The advantage with bands is that the tension builds and decreases exponentially. The bottom line: Train with a reverse band bench, and you can increase how much force you exert into the bar in your weakest points in the lift. 

